## 🛠️ Technology Stack

### **Core Technologies**

| Technology | Version | Purpose |
|------------|---------|---------|
| **Vue 3** | 3.3.8 | Reactive UI framework with Composition API |
| **Vite** | 5.0.0 | Lightning-fast dev server and build tool |
| **Tailwind CSS** | 3.3.6 | Utility-first CSS framework for styling |
| **Headless UI** | 1.7.16 | Accessible unstyled UI components |
| **Heroicons** | 2.0.18 | Beautiful SVG icons |
| **Pinia** | 2.1.7 | State management (modern Vuex replacement) |
| **Vue Router** | 4.2.5 | Client-side routing |

### **Why These Technologies?**

**Vue 3**:
- Reactive data binding (no manual DOM updates)
- Component-based architecture
- Easier to maintain than vanilla JavaScript
- Strong developer tools

**Vite**:
- Starts in <1 second (vs 10+ seconds for Webpack)
- Hot module replacement (instant updates on save)
- Optimized production builds

**Tailwind CSS**:
- Rapid styling with utility classes
- Consistent design system
- No CSS naming conflicts
- Smaller bundle size (unused styles removed)

**Headless UI**:
- Accessible by default (keyboard navigation, screen readers)
- Unstyled (full design control)
- Built by Tailwind team

**Pinia**:
- Simpler than Vuex
- Better TypeScript support
- DevTools integration for debugging

---

## 📁 Project Structure

```
frontend/
├── src/
│   ├── assets/
│   │   └── main.css                 # Tailwind imports + custom scrollbar
│   ├── components/                  # Reusable components (future)
│   ├── layouts/
│   │   └── AppLayout.vue           # Main layout with sidebar navigation
│   ├── views/                       # Page components (one per route)
│   │   ├── Auth.vue                # Login/Signup page
│   │   ├── Dashboard.vue           # Class grid homepage
│   │   ├── ClassPage.vue           # Individual class workspace
│   │   ├── Timetable.vue           # Weekly schedule
│   │   ├── Notifications.vue       # Alerts center
│   │   └── Settings.vue            # Account settings
│   ├── stores/
│   │   └── auth.js                 # Authentication state (Pinia)
│   ├── services/
│   │   └── api.js                  # Backend API client
│   ├── router/
│   │   └── index.js                # Route definitions + guards
│   ├── App.vue                     # Root component
│   └── main.js                     # Application entry point
├── index.html                       # HTML template
├── package.json                     # Dependencies
├── vite.config.js                  # Vite configuration
├── tailwind.config.js              # Tailwind theme (colors, fonts)
├── postcss.config.js               # PostCSS configuration
└── README.md                        # This file
```

### **Key Files Explained**

**`src/main.js`**: 
- Entry point of the application
- Initializes Vue, Pinia, and Router
- Mounts the app to `#app` div

**`src/router/index.js`**:
- Defines all routes (`/`, `/auth`, `/class/:id`, etc.)
- Authentication guards (redirect to login if not authenticated)

**`src/stores/auth.js`**:
- Manages authentication state (user, token)
- Functions: `login()`, `register()`, `logout()`, `updateUser()`
- Persists to localStorage

**`src/services/api.js`**:
- All backend API calls
- Handles authentication headers
- Error handling

**`src/layouts/AppLayout.vue`**:
- Sidebar navigation
- User profile dropdown
- Outlet for page content

