## 💻 Development Guide

### **Running the App**

```bash
# Development mode (hot reload)
npm run dev

# Build for production
npm run build

# Preview production build
npm run preview
```

### **Common Development Tasks**

**1. Adding a new page**:
```vue
<!-- src/views/NewPage.vue -->
<template>
  <div class="p-8">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-grey-900">New Page</h1>
  </div>
</template>

<script setup>
import { ref } from 'vue';

const message = ref('Hello!');
</script>
```

Then add route:
```javascript
// src/router/index.js
{
  path: '/new-page',
  name: 'NewPage',
  component: () => import('@/views/NewPage.vue'),
  meta: { requiresAuth: true }
}
```

**2. Making an API call**:
```javascript
import api from '@/services/api';

async function loadData() {
  try {
    const response = await api.getClasses();
    if (response.success) {
      classes.value = response.classes;
    }
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('Failed:', error);
  }
}
```

**3. Using Tailwind classes**:
```vue
<!-- Blue button with hover effect -->
<button class="bg-primary-600 hover:bg-primary-700 text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-lg transition">
  Click Me
</button>

<!-- Responsive grid (1 col mobile, 3 col desktop) -->
<div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
  <div>Item 1</div>
  <div>Item 2</div>
  <div>Item 3</div>
</div>
```

### **Code Style Guidelines**

**Vue Components**:
- Use `<script setup>` syntax
- Use Composition API (`ref`, `computed`, `onMounted`)
- Keep components under 300 lines
- Extract complex logic to composables

**Naming Conventions**:
- Components: PascalCase (`ClassCard.vue`)
- Variables: camelCase (`currentClass`)
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (`MAX_STUDENTS`)

**Tailwind**:
- Use utility classes, not custom CSS
- Follow order: layout → spacing → colors → typography
- Group related utilities: `"px-6 py-3"` not `"px-6 rounded-lg py-3"`

